You can use `sqlx` for async database interactions. It supports compile-time query validation and is performant. Here’s a small snippet to illustrate an async transaction using sqlx:

```rust
use sqlx::{postgres::PgPool, error::Error};

async fn run_tx(pool: &PgPool) -> Result<(), Error> {
    let mut tx = pool.begin().await?;
    sqlx::query("INSERT INTO users(name) VALUES(?)")
        .bind("Alice")
        .execute(&mut *tx)
        .await?;
    tx.commit().await?;
    Ok(())
}
```
